(24, 1, '2016-04-05 14:01:30', '2016-04-05 14:01:30', '<h2>WE</h2>\r\nWith its slogan <em>\"Think Eco! Live Eco! \", </em>Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping (ELL) was established with a professed two-pronged motive to:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Cater quality and state-of-the-art lawn and landscaping services in particular;</li>\r\n 	<li>Respond and contribute to rising environmental degradation brought in the wake of non-point source pollution (meaning pollution without an easily identifiable source)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOne of the key sources of non-point source pollutants are fertilizers, pesticides and several other synthetic products that we use in maintaining our lawn and landscaping. Numerous studies have shown that children are vulnerable to many lawn and garden Chemicals. \"Parents can make a big difference in their home. They have the power over the decision whether or not to use chemicals,\" says Dr. Philip F. Landrigan of the Mount Sinai School of Medicine.\r\n\r\nAccording to <em>Journal of the American Veterinary Medicine Association (April 2004)</em>, certain breed of dogs have been proved to significantly at risk from bladder cancer and a host of other ailments if they are exposed to lawn that are chemically-treated.\r\n\r\nAt this backdrop, we are proud to specialize in some of the newest technologies to cope with some of the sustainable issues such as water pollution, stormwater management, pesticide toxicity, soil health, and fertilizer runoff.\r\n\r\nWe are a full service, eco-friendly, economical and sustainable landscape company. We are committed to create beautiful and healthy landscapes preserving the earth\'s resources.\r\n<h2></h2>', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2016-07-05 13:16:13', '2016-07-05 13:16:13', '', 0, 'http://ecollc.dev/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(25, 1, '2016-04-07 11:28:48', '2016-04-07 11:28:48', '<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Mahesh Singh Dangol</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-806 size-medium\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-3-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client\'s often nickname him as \"Drainage Doctor\" for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\r\n\r\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor\'s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master\'s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\r\n\r\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.', 'Managing Director', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'managing-director', '', '', '2016-07-08 13:15:28', '2016-07-08 13:15:28', '', 24, 'http://ecollc.dev/?page_id=10', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(26, 1, '2016-04-07 11:31:46', '2016-04-07 11:31:46', '<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-618\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/services.jpg\" alt=\"Services\" width=\"870\" height=\"280\" />\r\n<h2>Our Services include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/lawn-care/\">Lawn/Bed Care</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/maintenance/\">Landscape Maintenance</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/landscape-design/\">Landscape Design</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/rain-garden/\">Rain Garden</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/drainage-doctor/\">Drainage Doctor</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"/our-services/snow-removal/\">Snow Removal</a></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Our Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'our-services', '', '', '2016-07-03 10:18:46', '2016-07-03 10:18:46', '', 0, 'http://ecollc.dev/?page_id=14', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(27, 1, '2016-04-07 11:32:19', '2016-04-07 11:32:19', '<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-812\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/faq-1.jpg\" alt=\"faq\" width=\"870\" height=\"280\" />\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[su_accordion]\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"What is meant by Organic?\"] “Organic” means landscaping without the application of synthetic pesticides of any kind (insecticides, herbicides, fungicides, etc.) and synthetic fertilizers or soil amendments.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"What does organic land care means?\"]Organic land care is a sustainable ecological landscaping system that promotes and enhances biodiversity, biological nutrient cycles, and soil biological activity. It is based on minimal use of off-­site inputs and on management practices that restore, maintain, and enhance ecological harmony and beauty in urban and suburban landscapes and gardens. [/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"What effect do synthetic fertilizers and pesticides on environment?\"]The chemicals used in synthetic fertilizers and pesticides destroy the naturally present beneficial organisms in the soil food web. This has a knock-on effect for plants that rely on these organisms to provide a balanced and healthy soil. Without a balanced soil, plants have to rely upon more and more external inputs of chemicals to obtain nutrients and to fend off pests and weeds.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"Are there any health risks associated with lawn care products?\"]There have been many scientific studies regarding negative health consequences of synthetic chemicals found in chemical fertilizers and pesticides [/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"Do synthetic fertilizers and pesticides contribute to water pollution?\"]Yes. Many states, including Virginia, have directly linked chemical leaching and run off to water pollution.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"How important is site analysis during initial phase?\"]Site Analysis is the primary discipline used to determine appropriate land use––including plant selection and placement, construction and placement of hardscape elements, and in some cases, site modification to create particular ecosystems. Design is the creative application of these principles in the landscape. It employs the disciplines of ecology and sustainability to create landscapes that can be managed organically.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"Is soil test necessary?\"]The foundation of organic land care is knowledge of and proper care for the soil. Soil tests, along with site analysis, allow the land care professional to select and implement practices that maintain or increase soil life and vitality and thereby enable the soil to support a vigorous plant community.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"Can I put lots of organic fertilizer and soil amendments?\"]Fertilizers and soil amendments are tools that enable us to modify existing soil conditions. The “feed the soil” principle is used to benefit plant health, not artificially stimulate plant growth. Unnecessary applications of any fertilizer or soil amendment can cause nutrients to build up to excessive levels in the soil. At such levels, nutrients may enter local water resources. Nitrogen and phosphorus are the nutrients most involved in eutrophication of water bodies (nitrogen in oceans, phosphorus in lakes and ponds), and are thus of major concern as pollutants. Nitrogen can also be a hazard to human health when it pollutes drinking water supplies.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"What is \'Compost Tea\'?\"]\'Compost Tea\' is the liquid derived from naturally decomposing organic material. Creating compost tea is usually referred to as \"Brewing\" .We produce our own worm casting for brewing compost tea.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"How much top dressing can be applied around turf, around perennial, and around shrubs and shade trees?\"]On turf: ¼ inch or less, no more than two times per year, for no more than three years, unless a soil test shows organic matter remains below 4% and phosphorus is below “medium” Around perennials: 2 inches or less Around shrubs and shade trees: 3 inches or less.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"What height should I cut my grass?\"]Turf­ type tall fescue and fine fescue grasses are best maintained when a mower cutting height is set at 3 1/2\". Maintaining grass at this height will help the grass plants through increased photosynthesis and help to crowd out weed seeds that will inevitably land on your lawn. Towards the end of the season (October) lower the cutting height to 2\" to help avoid winter damage. Zoysia grass is best maintained with a mowing height between 2\" and 3\".[/su_spoiler]\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"Should I leave grass clippings on the grass or remove them?\"]Grass clipping should be left on the grass as they quickly breakdown and provide a good source of natural nitrogen to the lawn. It is necessary to have healthy soil for this to be most effective because it is the micro­organisms in the soil that break down the grass clippings and render them into chemical forms that can be readily used by the grass.[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title=\"How long will it take for an organic lawn care program to be effective?\"]The length of time is directly related to the intensity of current and past synthetic management practices and overall turf quality. However, by immediately starting to address soil condition and using natural organic fertilizers the transition between a synthetic program and an organic program will be hardly noticeable.[/su_spoiler]\r\n[/su_accordion]', 'FAQ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faq', '', '', '2016-07-08 15:01:09', '2016-07-08 15:01:09', '', 0, 'http://ecollc.dev/?page_id=16', 0, 'page', '', 0),
