(593, 1, '2016-07-03 09:41:54', '2016-07-03 09:41:54', '<h2>Welcome to Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping, LLC</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-592\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/organic-300x123.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"123\" />\r\n\r\nWith its slogan <em>“Think Eco! Live Eco! “, </em>Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping (ELL) was established with a professed two-pronged motive to: a) Respond and contribute to rising environmental degradation brought in the wake of non-point source pollution (meaning pollution without an easily identifiable source) in general; b) Cater quality and state-of-the-art lawn and landscaping services in particular.\r\n\r\nWe are a full service, eco-friendly, economical and sustainable landscape company.  We specialize in some of the newest technologies to cope with some of the sustainable issues such as water pollution, stormwater management, pesticide toxicity, soil health, and fertilizer runoff. <a href=\"/about-us/\">Read More</a>', 'Home About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '218-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:41:54', '2016-07-03 09:41:54', '', 218, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/218-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(594, 1, '2016-07-03 09:44:14', '2016-07-03 09:44:14', '', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'mahesh-singh-dangol-blog', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:44:33', '2016-07-03 09:44:33', '', 351, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(595, 1, '2016-07-08 12:44:37', '2016-07-08 12:44:37', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Let\'s make a pledge and join hands to save Virginia from Non-source Pollution!</strong></em></p>\nOur valued Clients, well-wishers and Friends\n\n<em>Warmest Greetings!</em>\n\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-609 size-medium\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.  The road was not strewn with roses but the nobility of our mission to revive the \"organic splendor\" of Virginia prodded us to soldier on.\n\nNow, we have carved a niche with the only landscaping company that provides and campaigns for organic revolution in Virginia. Our efforts have been supported by environment-conscious Virginia denizens who have started adopting organic measures by discarding synthetic chemicals and fertilizers. The warm reception and the overwhelming response we got from our valued clients acts as a shot of adrenaline to us, thereby giving us the will to excel and innovate.\n\nOur slogan is: \"Think Eco! Live Eco!\" As we are all aware of the fact that the use of synthetic fertilizers and chemicals negatively impacts not only the health of our lawn and landscape but also animals, pets, our children and ourselves, it has become extremely necessary to adopt organic lifestyle.\n\nWe have started this blog especially as a tool to provide information to our clients in general and the issues of lawn and landscaping in particular. We will be sharing our experiences through this blog and expect feedback and comments.\n\nWith a renewed zeal to make Virginia an organic zone!\n\nOn behalf of ELL Family\n\nMahesh Singh Dangol\n\nManaging Director', 'A Commitment to Serve Virginia!', 'It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '351-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 12:44:37', '2016-07-08 12:44:37', '', 351, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/351-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(737, 1, '2016-07-03 13:23:14', '2016-07-03 13:23:14', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Let\'s make a pledge and join hands to save Virginia from Non-source Pollution!</strong></em></p>\r\nOur valued Clients, well-wishers and Friends\r\n\r\n<em>Warmest Greetings!</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.  The road was not strewn with roses but the nobility of our mission to revive the \"organic splendor\" of Virginia prodded us to soldier on.\r\n\r\nNow, we have carved a niche with the only landscaping company that provides and campaigns for organic revolution in Virginia. Our efforts have been supported by environment-conscious Virginia denizens who have started adopting organic measures by discarding synthetic chemicals and fertilizers. The warm reception and the overwhelming response we got from our valued clients acts as a shot of adrenaline to us, thereby giving us the will to excel and innovate.\r\n\r\nOur slogan is: \"Think Eco! Live Eco!\" As we are all aware of the fact that the use of synthetic fertilizers and chemicals negatively impacts not only the health of our lawn and landscape but also animals, pets, our children and ourselves, it has become extremely necessary to adopt organic lifestyle.\r\n\r\nWe have started this blog especially as a tool to provide information to our clients in general and the issues of lawn and landscaping in particular. We will be sharing our experiences through this blog and expect feedback and comments.\r\n\r\nWith a renewed zeal to make Virginia an organic zone!\r\n\r\nOn behalf of ELL Family\r\n\r\nMahesh Singh Dangol\r\n\r\nManaging Director', 'A Commitment to Serve Virginia!', 'It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '351-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 13:23:14', '2016-07-03 13:23:14', '', 351, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/351-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(596, 1, '2016-07-03 09:44:51', '2016-07-03 09:44:51', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Let\'s make a pledge and join hands to save Virginia from Non-source Pollution!</strong></em></p>\r\nOur valued Clients, well-wishers and Friends\r\n\r\n<em>Warmest Greetings!</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.  The road was not strewn with roses but the nobility of our mission to revive the \"organic splendor\" of Virginia prodded us to soldier on.\r\n\r\nNow, we have carved a niche with the only landscaping company that provides and campaigns for organic revolution in Virginia. Our efforts have been supported by environment-conscious Virginia denizens who have started adopting organic measures by discarding synthetic chemicals and fertilizers. The warm reception and the overwhelming response we got from our valued clients acts as a shot of adrenaline to us, thereby giving us the will to excel and innovate.\r\n\r\nOur slogan is: \"Think Eco! Live Eco!\" As we are all aware of the fact that the use of synthetic fertilizers and chemicals negatively impacts not only the health of our lawn and landscape but also animals, pets, our children and ourselves, it has become extremely necessary to adopt organic lifestyle.\r\n\r\nWe have started this blog especially as a tool to provide information to our clients in general and the issues of lawn and landscaping in particular. We will be sharing our experiences through this blog and expect feedback and comments.\r\n\r\nWith a renewed zeal to make Virginia an organic zone!\r\n\r\nOn behalf of ELL Family\r\n\r\nMahesh Singh Dangol\r\n\r\nManaging Director', 'A Commitment to Serve Virginia!', 'It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.  The road was not strewn with roses but the nobility of our mission to revive the \"organic splendor\" of Virginia prodded us to soldier on.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '351-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:44:51', '2016-07-03 09:44:51', '', 351, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/351-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(597, 1, '2016-07-03 09:46:35', '2016-07-03 09:46:35', '<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-297 alignright\" src=\"http://dev.habrenepal.com.np/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/logo-300x110.png\" alt=\"logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"110\" />\n<h2>WE</h2>\nWith its slogan <em>\"Think Eco! Live Eco! \", </em>Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping (ELL) was established with a professed two-pronged motive to:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Cater quality and state-of-the-art lawn and landscaping services in particular;</li>\n 	<li>Respond and contribute to rising environmental degradation brought in the wake of non-point source pollution (meaning pollution without an easily identifiable source)</li>\n</ol>\nOne of the key sources of non-point source pollutants are fertilizers, pesticides and several other synthetic products that we use in maintaining our lawn and landscaping. Numerous studies have shown that children are vulnerable to many lawn and garden Chemicals. \"Parents can make a big difference in their home. They have the power over the decision whether or not to use chemicals,\" says Dr. Philip F. Landrigan of the Mount Sinai School of Medicine.\n\nAccording to <em>Journal of the American Veterinary Medicine Association (April 2004)</em>, certain breed of dogs have been proved to significantly at risk from bladder cancer and a host of other ailments if they are exposed to lawn that are chemically-treated.\n\nAt this backdrop, we are proud to specialize in some of the newest technologies to cope with some of the sustainable issues such as water pollution, stormwater management, pesticide toxicity, soil health, and fertilizer runoff.\n\nWe are a full service, eco-friendly, economical and sustainable landscape company. We are committed to create beautiful and healthy landscapes preserving the earth\'s resources.\n<h2></h2>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '24-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:46:35', '2016-07-03 09:46:35', '', 24, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/24-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(783, 1, '2016-07-05 13:15:47', '2016-07-05 13:15:47', '&nbsp;\r\n<h2>WE</h2>\r\nWith its slogan <em>\"Think Eco! Live Eco! \", </em>Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping (ELL) was established with a professed two-pronged motive to:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Cater quality and state-of-the-art lawn and landscaping services in particular;</li>\r\n 	<li>Respond and contribute to rising environmental degradation brought in the wake of non-point source pollution (meaning pollution without an easily identifiable source)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOne of the key sources of non-point source pollutants are fertilizers, pesticides and several other synthetic products that we use in maintaining our lawn and landscaping. Numerous studies have shown that children are vulnerable to many lawn and garden Chemicals. \"Parents can make a big difference in their home. They have the power over the decision whether or not to use chemicals,\" says Dr. Philip F. Landrigan of the Mount Sinai School of Medicine.\r\n\r\nAccording to <em>Journal of the American Veterinary Medicine Association (April 2004)</em>, certain breed of dogs have been proved to significantly at risk from bladder cancer and a host of other ailments if they are exposed to lawn that are chemically-treated.\r\n\r\nAt this backdrop, we are proud to specialize in some of the newest technologies to cope with some of the sustainable issues such as water pollution, stormwater management, pesticide toxicity, soil health, and fertilizer runoff.\r\n\r\nWe are a full service, eco-friendly, economical and sustainable landscape company. We are committed to create beautiful and healthy landscapes preserving the earth\'s resources.\r\n<h2></h2>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-05 13:15:47', '2016-07-05 13:15:47', '', 24, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(598, 1, '2016-07-03 09:47:25', '2016-07-03 09:47:25', '<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-573\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/logo.png\" alt=\"Logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"110\" />\r\n<h2>WE</h2>\r\nWith its slogan <em>\"Think Eco! Live Eco! \", </em>Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping (ELL) was established with a professed two-pronged motive to:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Cater quality and state-of-the-art lawn and landscaping services in particular;</li>\r\n 	<li>Respond and contribute to rising environmental degradation brought in the wake of non-point source pollution (meaning pollution without an easily identifiable source)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOne of the key sources of non-point source pollutants are fertilizers, pesticides and several other synthetic products that we use in maintaining our lawn and landscaping. Numerous studies have shown that children are vulnerable to many lawn and garden Chemicals. \"Parents can make a big difference in their home. They have the power over the decision whether or not to use chemicals,\" says Dr. Philip F. Landrigan of the Mount Sinai School of Medicine.\r\n\r\nAccording to <em>Journal of the American Veterinary Medicine Association (April 2004)</em>, certain breed of dogs have been proved to significantly at risk from bladder cancer and a host of other ailments if they are exposed to lawn that are chemically-treated.\r\n\r\nAt this backdrop, we are proud to specialize in some of the newest technologies to cope with some of the sustainable issues such as water pollution, stormwater management, pesticide toxicity, soil health, and fertilizer runoff.\r\n\r\nWe are a full service, eco-friendly, economical and sustainable landscape company. We are committed to create beautiful and healthy landscapes preserving the earth\'s resources.\r\n<h2></h2>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:47:25', '2016-07-03 09:47:25', '', 24, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
