(609, 1, '2016-07-03 09:59:24', '2016-07-03 09:59:24', '', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'mahesh-singh-dangol-1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:59:52', '2016-07-03 09:59:52', '', 25, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(610, 1, '2016-07-03 09:59:56', '2016-07-03 09:59:56', '<h2>Mahesh Singh Dangol</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-609\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client\'s often nickname him as \"Drainage Doctor\" for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\r\n\r\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor\'s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master\'s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\r\n\r\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.', 'Managing Director', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 09:59:56', '2016-07-03 09:59:56', '', 25, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/25-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(611, 1, '2016-07-08 13:06:37', '2016-07-08 13:06:37', '<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-609\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" />With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client’s often nickname him as “Drainage Doctor” for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\n\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor’s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master’s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\n\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.\n\n<em><strong> </strong></em>', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '253-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 13:06:37', '2016-07-08 13:06:38', '', 253, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/253-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(612, 1, '2016-07-03 10:02:45', '2016-07-03 10:02:45', '<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client’s often nickname him as “Drainage Doctor” for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\r\n\r\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor’s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master’s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\r\n\r\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.\r\n\r\n<em><strong> </strong></em>', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'Mahesh Dangol', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '253-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 10:02:45', '2016-07-03 10:02:45', '', 253, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/253-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(613, 1, '2016-07-03 10:03:20', '2016-07-03 10:03:20', '<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-594\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-blog-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client’s often nickname him as “Drainage Doctor” for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\r\n\r\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor’s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master’s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\r\n\r\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.\r\n\r\n<em><strong> </strong></em>', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '253-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-03 10:03:20', '2016-07-03 10:03:20', '', 253, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/253-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
