(803, 1, '2016-07-08 12:43:59', '2016-07-08 12:43:59', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Let\'s make a pledge and join hands to save Virginia from Non-source Pollution!</strong></em></p>\r\nOur valued Clients, well-wishers and Friends\r\n\r\n<em>Warmest Greetings!</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-609 size-medium\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.  The road was not strewn with roses but the nobility of our mission to revive the \"organic splendor\" of Virginia prodded us to soldier on.\r\n\r\nNow, we have carved a niche with the only landscaping company that provides and campaigns for organic revolution in Virginia. Our efforts have been supported by environment-conscious Virginia denizens who have started adopting organic measures by discarding synthetic chemicals and fertilizers. The warm reception and the overwhelming response we got from our valued clients acts as a shot of adrenaline to us, thereby giving us the will to excel and innovate.\r\n\r\nOur slogan is: \"Think Eco! Live Eco!\" As we are all aware of the fact that the use of synthetic fertilizers and chemicals negatively impacts not only the health of our lawn and landscape but also animals, pets, our children and ourselves, it has become extremely necessary to adopt organic lifestyle.\r\n\r\nWe have started this blog especially as a tool to provide information to our clients in general and the issues of lawn and landscaping in particular. We will be sharing our experiences through this blog and expect feedback and comments.\r\n\r\nWith a renewed zeal to make Virginia an organic zone!\r\n\r\nOn behalf of ELL Family\r\n\r\nMahesh Singh Dangol\r\n\r\nManaging Director', 'A Commitment to Serve Virginia!', 'It has been three years since the \"Eco-Friendly Lawn and Landscaping\" (ELL) started providing its services in Virginia. In the buzzing crowd of landscaping companies, we initially felt lost with obvious teething troubles and our inability to grasp the nuances of the trade.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '351-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 12:43:59', '2016-07-08 12:43:59', '', 351, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/351-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(805, 1, '2016-07-08 13:07:22', '2016-07-08 13:07:22', '<a href=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-609 size-medium\" src=\"http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Mahesh-Singh-Dangol-1-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Mahesh Singh Dangol\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>With an experience spanning more than a decade in lawn and landscaping domain, Mahesh Singh Dangol is an exemplary leader of the company. He also commands a deft hand in stormwater management and patio-designing. Client’s often nickname him as “Drainage Doctor” for his unparalleled expertise in drainage system repair and maintenance.\r\n\r\nA lover of nature in its pristine glory and a die-hard green campaigner, Mr. Singh holds double bachelor’s degrees in Environmental Biology and Environmental Science. He is also pursuing master’s degree in landscape Architecture. He is the rare kind who blends time-tried traditional methods with state-of-the art technologies to come up with innovative solutions. He also worked under Exotic Plant Management Group, Shenandoah National Park, Luray, Virginia.\r\n\r\nLicensed and certified to do all types landscaping-related jobs, he has proven ability in preparing detailed drawing of plans, elevations and sections and has high experience in AutoCAD, Photoshop, sketch up and AC GIS in developing exceptional presentation and 3D renderings.\r\n\r\n<em><strong> </strong></em>', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'Mahesh Singh Dangol', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '253-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 13:07:22', '2016-07-08 13:07:22', '', 253, 'http://ecolawnlandscaping.com/253-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
